1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,295
[Ahmad] <i>I'll get you into the NLEA</i>
<i>as an honorable,</i>

2
00:00:04,379 --> 00:00:06,297
<i>clean, and capable police officer.</i>

3
00:00:06,381 --> 00:00:07,549
[Azuelo] <i>This is Major Espina.</i>

4
00:00:07,632 --> 00:00:11,302
<i>He's the special liaison officer</i>
<i>sent to us by Muslim Affairs.</i>

5
00:00:11,386 --> 00:00:13,179
[Marcus] <i>What's the deal</i>
<i>with this liaison from Mindanao?</i>

6
00:00:13,263 --> 00:00:14,848
<i>Why are all his files redacted?</i>

7
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:16,599
[Lara] <i>Who's protecting you?</i>

8
00:00:17,183 --> 00:00:19,102
[Jalil] <i>I need to finish my mission.</i>

9
00:00:19,185 --> 00:00:21,354
<i>For my father, and for our town.</i>

10
00:00:21,438 --> 00:00:24,190
- [Marcus] <i>Why are you following me?</i>
- [Jalil] <i>I'm just doing my job.</i>

11
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:27,402
[Felix] <i>You don't have to worry</i>
<i>about anything anymore, Boss.</i>

12
00:00:27,485 --> 00:00:29,654
<i>I've cleaned up all the loose ends.</i>

13
00:00:29,738 --> 00:00:32,240
<i>Espina won't find anything.</i>

14
00:00:32,323 --> 00:00:35,910
[Manuel] <i>I know you have feelings</i>
<i>for Lara.</i>

15
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:38,204
<i>I don't want her getting hurt</i>

16
00:00:38,288 --> 00:00:43,376
<i>if she gets in the way of our plans.</i>

17
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:47,130
[Jalil] <i>The more I learn,</i>
<i>the more questions I have.</i>

18
00:00:47,213 --> 00:00:50,842
<i>But I know I'm in the right place.</i>
<i>I'll save you, Father,</i>

19
00:00:50,925 --> 00:00:53,928
<i>and I'll find out who's behind</i>
<i>all of this.</i>

20
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:57,223
[officer] <i>Our police are in a shootout</i>
<i>with robbers at Centro Heritage Bank.</i>

21
00:00:57,307 --> 00:00:59,100
<i>They're requesting</i>
<i>specialized intervention.</i>

22
00:00:59,184 --> 00:01:01,186
[suspenseful music playing]

23
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:03,188
[man grunts]

24
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:08,359
[tires screeching]

25
00:01:09,069 --> 00:01:10,570
[Lara, in English] <i>Alpha 1, this is Base.</i>

26
00:01:10,653 --> 00:01:12,489
[in English] <i>We have a visual</i>
<i>on the target, a black van heading east.</i>

27
00:01:13,156 --> 00:01:15,909
He's losing too much blood.
What do we do?!

28
00:01:15,992 --> 00:01:17,786
Wait, I'm thinking!

29
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:19,496
[suspenseful music playing]

30
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:21,873
The TFA!

31
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:24,667
- Move!
- Wait!

32
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:26,961
[Marcus] <i>We need eyes on the target.</i>
<i>We've lost them.</i>

33
00:01:27,712 --> 00:01:31,216
[Lara] <i>Marcus, they're heading south.</i>
<i>They're going to…</i>

34
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:34,719
<i>Marcus, they're entering…</i>
<i>S. Trinidad Hospital.</i>

35
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:40,058
Nobody move! Nobody move!

36
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:42,268
[man 1] <i>I said nobody move!</i>

37
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:43,353
[man 2] <i>Hey, hey!</i>

38
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:47,065
[suspenseful music continues]

39
00:01:51,694 --> 00:01:58,493
[mysterious theme music playing]

40
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:08,461
[overlapping clamor]

41
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:09,838
[suspenseful music playing]

42
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:11,965
[overlapping clamor]

43
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:13,758
[man 1] Move aside!

44
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:14,634
[man 2] Hurry up!

45
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:16,010
- [man 3] Hey!
- [rapid gunfire]

46
00:02:16,094 --> 00:02:18,054
- [man 1] Hey!
- [man 2] Get over there!

47
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,597
[man 1] Come on!

48
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:20,723
[man 1] Get down!

49
00:02:21,724 --> 00:02:23,601
- [man 2] Out!
- [man 3] Out, out!

50
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:25,728
- [man 1] Move!
- [man 2] Everyone, get out!

51
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:26,813
[man 3] Hurry!

52
00:02:27,313 --> 00:02:32,277
[ominous music playing]

53
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,945
‪[frustrated grunt]

54
00:02:34,028 --> 00:02:38,324
- Domingo, hurry up!
- Yes, sir! I'm on it!

55
00:02:38,408 --> 00:02:41,035
[tense music playing]

56
00:02:41,119 --> 00:02:43,580
Why did Agent Reyes sound like that?

57
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:45,498
What's at S. Trinidad Hospital?

58
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:48,835
Sir, his mother is a doctor
at that hospital.

59
00:02:51,296 --> 00:02:55,049
[tense music playing]

60
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:01,097
[relieved sigh]

61
00:03:04,934 --> 00:03:08,104
[Jalil] <i>Thank you… Thank you so much.</i>

62
00:03:11,149 --> 00:03:15,069
[Teresa] Omar,
my son from SID is heading home.

63
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:16,279
We're leaving now, Doctor.

64
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:17,697
- [Jamilah] <i>Let's go.</i>
- [Omar] <i>Come on.</i>

65
00:03:19,157 --> 00:03:21,534
[Teresa] <i>Careful, okay?</i>
<i>Your wound might open.</i>

66
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:27,415
[tense music continues]

67
00:03:28,374 --> 00:03:30,460
- Sir, sir, please have mercy!
- [man] Oh…

68
00:03:30,543 --> 00:03:31,628
[grunts]

69
00:03:31,711 --> 00:03:36,507
[ominous music playing]

70
00:03:40,136 --> 00:03:41,888
- [line ringing]
- Hello, boss.

71
00:03:41,971 --> 00:03:43,348
I'm here in the security room.

72
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:46,059
Keep a close eye on the TFA.

73
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:50,980
If anyone gets in here,
I'll kill everyone inside!

74
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:55,944
[ominous music continues]

75
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:09,457
[suspenseful music playing]

76
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:11,709
Hands up! Nobody move!

77
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:16,923
[overlapping clamor]

78
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:19,425
- [grunting, coughing]
- Brother.

79
00:04:19,509 --> 00:04:21,344
[Tommy gasping]

80
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:23,304
Brother. Hey, hey.

81
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:27,267
[line ringing]

82
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,852
[phone vibrating]

83
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,356
He needs a doctor.

84
00:04:34,148 --> 00:04:35,608
[phone vibrating]

85
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:37,443
[whispers] Marcus. Hello, son?

86
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:38,611
[Tommy gasping]

87
00:04:39,737 --> 00:04:41,364
- He needs a doctor!
- [Axl] Doctor.

88
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:44,492
- Axl.
- Who's a doctor here?

89
00:04:45,576 --> 00:04:47,620
Who's a doctor here?!

90
00:04:47,704 --> 00:04:49,289
[ominous music continues]

91
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:53,876
[Axl] What are you doing? Huh?!

92
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:56,587
Take their phones!

93
00:04:57,171 --> 00:04:58,798
- [Axl] <i>Take them!</i>
- [overlapping clamor]

94
00:04:58,881 --> 00:04:59,966
[man 1] <i>Give me your phones!</i>

95
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:02,302
- [man 1] Take their phones!
- [man 2] Hurry!

96
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:05,471
- [man 1] Your phone!
- [man 2] The phones!

97
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:07,348
[line beeps]

98
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:09,475
[disgruntled huff, panting]

99
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:16,190
Agent Angeles! I need to see
what's happening inside.

100
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:19,527
My mother isn't the only one in there.
There are other hostages inside.

101
00:05:20,069 --> 00:05:21,237
[in English] We're on it.

102
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:23,323
- Buster, hack into the hospital's CCTV.
- [system beeping]

103
00:05:23,406 --> 00:05:24,615
[in English] Working on it, ma'am.

104
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:27,702
- [ominous music continues]
- [system beeping]

105
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:30,913
[thuds]

106
00:05:34,042 --> 00:05:37,211
[Axl] You're a doctor! Treat my brother!

107
00:05:37,295 --> 00:05:39,380
[Teresa grunting]

108
00:05:39,464 --> 00:05:42,759
Let the patients go. They're innocent!

109
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:45,344
[Jovi, indistinct]

110
00:05:45,428 --> 00:05:49,140
[ominous music continues]

111
00:05:49,223 --> 00:05:50,725
- [Teresa shrieks]
- [Jamilah] Doctor!

112
00:05:51,809 --> 00:05:53,102
[Axl] You've got guts!

113
00:05:54,896 --> 00:06:00,151
We're carrying guns,
and you're still making demands? Huh?

114
00:06:00,234 --> 00:06:04,238
Treat my brother,
and make sure he recovers!

115
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:07,241
If not, I'll kill them all!

116
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:10,870
[ominous music continues]

117
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:12,121
[in English] Seventy-two…

118
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:13,039
‪[system beeping]

119
00:06:13,706 --> 00:06:14,624
[in English] Eighty-eight…

120
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:17,126
[in English] Ninety-three…

121
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:24,926
[ominous music continues]

122
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:29,764
[in English] Connect this to the team.

123
00:06:30,681 --> 00:06:31,891
[Buster, in English] Copy, ma'am.

124
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:39,273
- [in English] Alpha 1, check your phones.
- [radio static]

125
00:06:48,449 --> 00:06:53,287
[ominous music continues]

126
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:01,337
You bastard! [hiss]

127
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:05,216
[music intensifies]

128
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:10,346
[Lara] Marcus!
Don't let this affect you! Calm down!

129
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:12,849
Don't worry about me, Lara.

130
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:17,061
[tense music continues]

131
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,189
- [Teresa grunts]
- [Jamilah] Doctor!

132
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:23,860
Do you think your brother
will be treated properly

133
00:07:24,777 --> 00:07:27,363
if you keep scaring everyone here?

134
00:07:27,864 --> 00:07:30,783
[tense music continues]

135
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,513
You think you're brave?

136
00:07:58,352 --> 00:08:03,691
[tense music continues]

137
00:08:28,174 --> 00:08:29,300
Stop!

138
00:08:30,801 --> 00:08:32,345
I'll operate on your brother.

139
00:08:32,428 --> 00:08:34,388
[Teresa] <i>Just don't hurt anybody.</i>

140
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:40,353
[tense music continues]

141
00:08:40,436 --> 00:08:42,730
- [Axl] Come here! Faster!
- Jamilah…

142
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:45,983
[thuds]

143
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:47,944
[Usman] Sir, what happened?

144
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:53,908
They're hurting innocent people.

145
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:56,160
We have to help them.

146
00:08:56,244 --> 00:09:00,373
Sir, that's why we're here.
To help and save them.

147
00:09:00,456 --> 00:09:03,000
So, don't worry. We're almost there.

148
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:05,711
- Hurry up!
- [in English] Yes, sir.

149
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:09,882
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil!</i>

150
00:09:10,758 --> 00:09:12,343
- [Jalil] <i>Jamilah!</i>
- [Jamilah chuckles]

151
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:18,099
[tense music continues]

152
00:09:20,726 --> 00:09:22,144
[Jamilah] <i>You know me, Jalil.</i>

153
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:26,941
If you don't let me help,
I'd go find Papa myself.

154
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:35,658
[Jalil] <i>Wait for me, Jamilah.</i>

155
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:37,201
<i>I'm going to save you.</i>

156
00:09:37,994 --> 00:09:42,081
[music intensifies]

157
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:48,421
[Axl] Move faster if you don't
want to go to hell with us!

158
00:09:48,504 --> 00:09:49,672
Move!

159
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:51,507
[indistinct chattering]

160
00:09:52,758 --> 00:09:54,135
[in English] Jamilah, gloves.

161
00:09:54,218 --> 00:09:56,512
‪-[tense music playing]
‪-[rubber glove snaps]

162
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:57,763
[in English] Scissors.

163
00:09:58,431 --> 00:09:59,807
- [Tommy gasps]
- [indistinct speech]

164
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:02,018
[unsettling music playing]

165
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:05,938
[engine revving]

166
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:08,357
[line rings]

167
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:15,031
- [in English] Lidocaine.
- [Jamilah] Here.

168
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:20,328
[Tommy groans in pain]

169
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:22,455
[Axl] Hang on, Tommy.

170
00:10:22,538 --> 00:10:24,540
You're going to live.
We're going to get out of here.

171
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:27,752
Yes, Tommy. We won't leave you behind.

172
00:10:32,381 --> 00:10:36,302
- [music turns suspenseful]
- [Tommy groans]

173
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:40,181
[tires screech]

174
00:10:44,518 --> 00:10:45,519
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [man gasps]

175
00:10:52,109 --> 00:10:55,363
[suspenseful music continues]

176
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:02,286
[in English] Listen up, everyone!

177
00:11:02,953 --> 00:11:07,875
All hostages and suspects
are in the emergency room.

178
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:11,212
[in English] Our objective now,
secure the perimeter.

179
00:11:11,712 --> 00:11:13,130
Suarez, Cruz.

180
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:16,008
[in English] Seal the entry point.

181
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:18,302
- [in English] Copy, sir.
- [in English] Move!

182
00:11:19,136 --> 00:11:23,891
[suspenseful music continues]

183
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:35,820
- [Tommy gasps]
- [machine beeping]

184
00:11:39,615 --> 00:11:40,699
[in English] Scalpel.

185
00:11:43,994 --> 00:11:44,954
[in English] Cutting…

186
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:45,996
‪[flesh squelching]

187
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,540
‪[music intensifying, concludes]

188
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:55,631
- Jovi, are those ready?
- [gun clicking]

189
00:11:56,966 --> 00:11:58,092
All good.

190
00:11:58,634 --> 00:12:00,386
[pensive music playing]

191
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:03,097
We'll earn a lot from this.

192
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:06,517
This'll probably be our last gig ever.

193
00:12:07,059 --> 00:12:08,394
After this one…

194
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:11,730
we can change our lives completely.

195
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:14,775
So, we can't fail now.

196
00:12:16,444 --> 00:12:17,445
‪[Jovi sniffs]

197
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:21,031
- Axl, Jovi…
- Hey…

198
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:25,035
- Can I go with you? I want to help.
- [gun clicks]

199
00:12:25,119 --> 00:12:27,538
- No.
- Why not?

200
00:12:27,621 --> 00:12:30,666
Tommy, just listen to Axl. We got this.

201
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:32,501
No, I want to come, too.

202
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:35,004
Who's going to protect you?

203
00:12:35,504 --> 00:12:36,755
Just me, remember?

204
00:12:39,508 --> 00:12:42,386
- [Axl] <i>You're getting arrogant, huh?</i>
- [Tommy chuckles] <i>Ow! Axl!</i>

205
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:44,346
[Tommy] <i>That's settled, then!</i>
<i>I'm coming with you!</i>

206
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:46,348
[Tommy] <i>Alright? Cheers!</i>

207
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:52,104
- [patient monitor beeps]
- [Jamilah] Doc…

208
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:54,482
[in English] BP, 80 over 60.

209
00:12:54,565 --> 00:12:56,817
[tense music playing]

210
00:12:56,901 --> 00:12:59,111
What's going on? Tell us!

211
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:00,696
- [Teresa] Double the a-line.
- [Jamilah] Yes, Doc.

212
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:01,780
What's going on?!

213
00:13:02,364 --> 00:13:06,410
I can't operate on your brother
if you keep pointing a gun to my head!

214
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:09,997
If you want to save your brother,
calm down!

215
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:12,583
The doctor knows what she's doing.

216
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:14,293
Just trust us!

217
00:13:14,376 --> 00:13:18,923
- [machine beeping steadily]
- [pensive music playing]

218
00:13:19,590 --> 00:13:20,549
Hold on, Tommy.

219
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:23,552
Hold on!

220
00:13:24,178 --> 00:13:26,805
We will do everything
to save your brother.

221
00:13:29,225 --> 00:13:32,144
- [in English] Forceps.
- Here, doc.

222
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:34,855
[suspenseful music playing]

223
00:13:37,775 --> 00:13:39,443
Lara, I need the hospital's blueprint.

224
00:13:40,819 --> 00:13:43,280
[Lara, in English] We're on it.
Buster, blueprint.

225
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:44,532
[in English] Roger, ma'am.

226
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:50,538
[suspenseful music continues]

227
00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:52,081
‪[machine beeping steadily]

228
00:13:52,164 --> 00:13:53,666
[Teresa, in English] I cannot find it.

229
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:56,293
[in English] I cannot find it!

230
00:13:57,336 --> 00:13:58,379
[Teresa sighs]

231
00:13:58,462 --> 00:13:59,755
[in English] Suction.

232
00:13:59,838 --> 00:14:02,007
- [machine beeping steadily]
- [machine sucks]

233
00:14:04,218 --> 00:14:05,302
- [patient monitor beeps]
- [Jamilah] Doc.

234
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:07,263
[in English] BP, 75 over 50.

235
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:08,180
‪[music intensifies]

236
00:14:10,766 --> 00:14:13,519
Reyes, why are they here?

237
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:16,105
It's because of your mother's patient,
right?

238
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:18,023
They still came here,

239
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:20,150
even though they knew
they were going to be trapped.

240
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:22,653
That's how important the patient is.

241
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:25,865
[in English] I have it.

242
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:28,534
[tense music playing]

243
00:14:28,617 --> 00:14:29,869
Is he alright?

244
00:14:33,789 --> 00:14:35,249
[patient monitor beeps rapidly]

245
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:38,961
[in English] Clamp.

246
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:49,430
- [computer beeps]
- Ma'am…

247
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:50,347
‪[system beeping]

248
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:55,311
[Lara] <i>Agent Reyes,</i>
<i>I've identified the patient.</i>

249
00:14:55,394 --> 00:14:58,856
He's Tommy Rosales, the youngest brother
of Axl and Jovi Rosales.

250
00:14:58,939 --> 00:15:02,067
They're members of the notorious
criminal group, Metal-13.

251
00:15:03,944 --> 00:15:07,156
- [in English] Copy.
- Reyes, this is not a hostage-taking.

252
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,866
[Jalil] This was not in their plan.

253
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:11,493
They're in a race against time
to save their brother,

254
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:13,746
and we can't give them that luxury.

255
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:17,041
Let's just go!
It's the perfect time to attack.

256
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,793
Espina, listen to me.

257
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:21,879
We can't rush into things like that.

258
00:15:21,962 --> 00:15:23,589
There are civilians inside.

259
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:27,635
- [English] We have to negotiate with them.
- What?

260
00:15:28,427 --> 00:15:30,888
Do you really think
they'd negotiate with us?

261
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:35,768
We will use the negotiations
to distract them before we attack.

262
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:39,438
You should have said earlier.

263
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:42,024
You should've asked.

264
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:47,029
[music intensifies]

265
00:15:53,619 --> 00:15:56,830
[monitor beeping rapidly]

266
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:57,748
[Jovi] What's happening?

267
00:15:58,874 --> 00:16:01,335
- What's happening?!
- What did you do to him?!

268
00:16:01,418 --> 00:16:03,462
[people weeping]

269
00:16:03,545 --> 00:16:08,217
If you don't save our brother,
we'll blow your head off!

270
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:11,095
[suspenseful sting]

271
00:16:11,178 --> 00:16:12,012
‪[system beeping]

272
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:15,307
- Marcus!
- What is it, Lara?

273
00:16:17,101 --> 00:16:18,435
Brother.

274
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:24,316
[tense music playing]

275
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:27,778
- [monitor beeping]
- <i>Move! Move!</i>

276
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:32,491
[hospital staff crying from phone]

277
00:16:32,574 --> 00:16:33,409
‪[music intensifies]

278
00:16:39,248 --> 00:16:45,796
[Marcus breathing heavily]

279
00:16:47,297 --> 00:16:48,298
[shouts]

280
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,801
You don't have a plan?! Huh?!

281
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:54,805
[Marcus grunts]

282
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:57,766
Reyes! Reyes!

283
00:16:59,143 --> 00:17:00,185
Just be patient.

284
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:02,896
He's just calming himself down
before doing anything.

285
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:06,233
[tense music continues]

286
00:17:06,316 --> 00:17:07,151
‪[system beeping]

287
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:11,655
- [tense music playing]
- [digital trilling]

288
00:17:11,739 --> 00:17:14,867
[monitor beeping steadily]

289
00:17:30,674 --> 00:17:31,842
[Teresa] Hemostat.

290
00:17:37,514 --> 00:17:38,432
Suture.

291
00:17:38,515 --> 00:17:40,684
[Jamilah sighs]

292
00:17:42,394 --> 00:17:44,563
[breathing heavily]

293
00:17:44,646 --> 00:17:50,152
- [Lara sighs]
- [digital trilling]

294
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:53,906
[in English] Good job, Ma!

295
00:17:53,989 --> 00:17:59,119
[tense music continues]

296
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,503
[Jalil] <i>Stay strong.</i>

297
00:18:08,212 --> 00:18:10,798
<i>I'll be there soon. I'll save you.</i>

298
00:18:10,881 --> 00:18:12,257
‪[monitor beeping steadily]

299
00:18:21,391 --> 00:18:22,351
[Jalil] What now, Reyes?!

300
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:24,478
We're running out of time.

301
00:18:24,561 --> 00:18:28,107
Their brother is already safe.
Are we still gonna keep waiting?

302
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:32,194
[in English] Agent Angeles,
where's my negotiator?

303
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:35,781
[Azuelo] Agent Angeles! What's going on?

304
00:18:35,864 --> 00:18:38,408
This mission has to be successful!

305
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:40,744
[in English] All eyes are on us!

306
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:44,164
[Azuelo] <i>We can't afford to fail</i>
<i>with this hostage-taking!</i>

307
00:18:45,415 --> 00:18:48,001
[in English] Agent Reyes,
your negotiator just arrived.

308
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:51,338
- [radio static]
- [Marcus] <i>Good. Get him to work.</i>

309
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:53,549
[in English] What?

310
00:18:54,049 --> 00:18:57,094
[ball pen clicking rapidly]

311
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:03,600
[in English] Okay, team, listen up!

312
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:06,812
[Jalil] This is the only way we can enter
without being noticed.

313
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:10,315
I know.

314
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:16,363
[in English] Okay! Everyone, get ready.

315
00:19:16,446 --> 00:19:21,368
- [tense music continues]
- [monitor beeping steadily]

316
00:19:25,289 --> 00:19:26,456
It's over.

317
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:30,127
Your brother is safe.

318
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:35,757
[somber music playing]

319
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:57,487
[somber music continues]

320
00:19:57,571 --> 00:19:58,780
Doc.

321
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,950
Are you alright?

322
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:03,160
[sighs shakily]

323
00:20:06,121 --> 00:20:07,331
[sniffles]

324
00:20:07,956 --> 00:20:10,542
[somber music playing]

325
00:20:12,169 --> 00:20:15,380
[sobbing] I once lost a son before.

326
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:17,424
There are times when I wish that…

327
00:20:18,926 --> 00:20:20,427
he's still alive.

328
00:20:22,596 --> 00:20:27,476
Maybe I could have saved him
just like how I save my patients.

329
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:29,603
- Doc…
- [Teresa sobs]

330
00:20:29,686 --> 00:20:35,484
[somber music continues]

331
00:20:43,492 --> 00:20:45,494
[suspenseful sting]

332
00:20:45,577 --> 00:20:50,999
[ominous music playing]

333
00:21:01,343 --> 00:21:02,719
[suspenseful sting]

334
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:05,514
[suspenseful sting]

335
00:21:07,557 --> 00:21:13,105
<i>The hostage-taking situation</i>
<i>is still at S. Trinidad Hospital.</i>

336
00:21:13,188 --> 00:21:15,607
<i>The suspects are identified</i>
<i>to be Metal-13,</i>

337
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:20,445
<i>a notorious group of bandits</i>
<i>who are wanted all over the country.</i>

338
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:25,784
<i>They got trapped after forcibly rushing</i>
<i>their youngest brother, Tommy Rosales,</i>

339
00:21:25,867 --> 00:21:28,203
<i>who got shot after a shootout</i>

340
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:30,455
<i>at the Sentro Heritage Bank earlier today.</i>

341
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:32,791
- S. Trinidad Hospital?!
- You're right!

342
00:21:32,874 --> 00:21:35,002
Doesn't Jamilah work there, Omar?

343
00:21:35,085 --> 00:21:38,088
- [overlapping chatter]
- Soraya!

344
00:21:38,630 --> 00:21:39,965
- Soraya!
- Where are you going?

345
00:21:40,048 --> 00:21:42,009
To the S. Trinidad Hospital, of course.

346
00:21:42,092 --> 00:21:43,552
I just went back
'cause I forgot something.

347
00:21:43,635 --> 00:21:45,512
- Soraya!
- Look at the news!

348
00:21:45,595 --> 00:21:48,056
There's a hostage-taking at your hospital!

349
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:50,225
- Watch this!
- Soraya!

350
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:51,810
Look at the news!

351
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:53,478
[crying] Why did our hospital
get involved?!

352
00:21:53,562 --> 00:21:54,855
[Norhana] Did you see Jamilah there?

353
00:21:54,938 --> 00:21:56,815
- Is Jamilah at the hospital?
- [indistinct speech]

354
00:21:56,898 --> 00:21:58,150
Jalil, please answer!

355
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:00,902
[tense music playing]

356
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:02,821
[female reporter] <i>Metal-13 is armed</i>

357
00:22:02,904 --> 00:22:07,743
<i>with high-caliber firearms,</i>
<i>its sources still unknown.</i>

358
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:10,704
<i>Due to this,</i>
<i>the police forces were alarmed</i>

359
00:22:10,787 --> 00:22:13,665
<i>for the country's national security</i>

360
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:16,710
<i>for the widespread distribution</i>
<i>of illegal firearms</i>

361
00:22:16,793 --> 00:22:18,420
<i>from different syndicates.</i>

362
00:22:18,503 --> 00:22:23,759
[tense music playing]

363
00:22:40,233 --> 00:22:46,615
- [tense music continues]
- [dramatic stinging]

364
00:22:53,663 --> 00:22:57,626
[Ahmad] <i>This bank robbery</i>
<i>that led to a hostage-taking,</i>

365
00:22:57,709 --> 00:22:59,336
<i>someone is controlling them.</i>

366
00:22:59,419 --> 00:23:01,505
<i>This is all planned by someone.</i>

367
00:23:01,588 --> 00:23:04,132
[Jovi] Carefully look out for the CCTVs.

368
00:23:04,216 --> 00:23:06,259
[Jovi] <i>Keep a close eye on the TFA!</i>

369
00:23:07,803 --> 00:23:09,930
[Azuelo] I'll let you all
get out of there alive

370
00:23:10,013 --> 00:23:12,474
if you keep your hands
off of the hostages.

371
00:23:12,557 --> 00:23:13,809
Send us a helicopter.

372
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:16,728
In 30 minutes,
everyone here will drop dead.

373
00:23:16,812 --> 00:23:19,397
[in English] Marcus, you have 30 minutes.
Thirty minutes.

374
00:23:20,148 --> 00:23:22,192
I'll take care of this. Go on ahead.

375
00:23:22,275 --> 00:23:24,611
Major Espina, slow down.
There's some movement to your right.

376
00:23:24,694 --> 00:23:26,905
[grunting]

377
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:30,534
[grunts]

378
00:23:31,201 --> 00:23:32,786
This is a destabilization.

379
00:23:35,997 --> 00:23:38,708
- We'll blow all of your heads off!
- [people weep]

380
00:23:38,792 --> 00:23:41,128
[tense music playing]

381
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:42,212
[grunts]
